<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In August 2018, Elon Musk, the chief executive=
 officer and largest shareholder of Tesla Inc., <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMDgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWhhcy1zb21lLWZ1bi13=
aXRoLXRlc2xhP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXR=
tX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdH=
VmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB596d1f53" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  tweeted</a>: =E2=80=9CAm =
considering taking Tesla private at $420. Funding secured.=E2=80=9D As has =
by now been pretty exhaustively documented, he=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</em>consi=
dering taking Tesla private at $420 per share, but he did=C2=A0<em>not=C2=
=A0</em>have funding secured. He ended up not pursuing the transaction, ost=
ensibly because shareholders didn=E2=80=99t like it, though also possibly b=
ecause the transaction structure he had in mind =E2=80=94=C2=A0one in which=
 Tesla somehow became =E2=80=9Cprivate=E2=80=9D but <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMTMvZnVuZGluZy1mb3ItZWxvbi1tdXNr=
LXMtdGVzbGEtYnV5b3V0LXdhc24tdC1zby1zZWN1cmU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNjIzX01PTkVZU1R=
VRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMj=
A2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB846ab5a0" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  kept all of its existing shareholders</a>? =E2=80=94=C2=A0was not actu=
ally possible, or perhaps because he got bored with the idea and moved on t=
o his next provocation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If he=C2=A0<em>had=C2=A0</em>decided to push a=
head with the idea, would he have been able to raise the necessary $60 bill=
ion or so to finance the deal? I dunno, maybe? At the time that seemed like=
 a lot of money. Tesla=E2=80=99s market capitalization last Friday was $601=
 billion, though, so in hindsight buying it =E2=80=94=C2=A0or financing Mus=
k=E2=80=99s plan to buy it =E2=80=94=C2=A0in 2018=C2=A0would have worked ou=
t well. And Musk does seem to be <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30470906.258449/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMjQvZWxvbi1tdXNrLW5ldmVyLWpva2VzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDY=
yM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV=
90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd=
d078aa0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">
pretty good at raising money</a>. And, at the time of his tweet, he had had=
=C2=A0preliminary conversations with Saudi Arabia=E2=80=99s Public Investme=
nt Fund=C2=A0about financing the deal. They had enough money to do it. It=
=E2=80=99s not unreasonable to think that he could have gotten the money.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Musk tweeted, Tesla=E2=80=99s stock went=
=C2=A0up. It had been trading at about $340 per share shortly before his tw=
eet, and traded up to about $380 shortly after; it soon sank back below=C2=
=A0the unaffected price. The US Securities and Exchange Commission quickly =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDktMjgvbXVza=
y1zLXRlc2xhLWZ1bi1kb2VzLW5vdC1hbXVzZS1zZWM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjA=
2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa1a504d8" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">  sued Musk for securities fraud</a>, arguing that funding was not secure=
d; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMTAtMDEvdG=
VzbGEtd2lsbC10cnktdG8tYmUtbW9yZS1ub3JtYWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVR=
kYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjA2=
JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB555b7d4f" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>  Musk=C2=A0settled</a> for a=C2=A0fine and a promise not to tweet materia=
l things about Tesla unless a lawyer reviewed them first. (He promptly <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDItMjcvd2hvLWNhb=
i1zYXktd2hhdC1jYWxpZm9ybmlhLW1lYW5zP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNiZ1dG1=
fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5157f3f4" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  fo=
rgot about that</a>.)=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also though some shareholders who bought the s=
tock at its elevated post-tweet price sued Musk for fraud, arguing that the=
y were deceived by his tweets. That case took a long time, but on Friday a =
jury <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.2584=
49/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDMvbXVz=
ay1qdXJ5LXJlYWNoZXMtdmVyZGljdC1pbi10ZXNsYS10d2VldC1mcmF1ZC10cmlhbC1jb3VydC1=
zYXlzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdX=
JjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5b35775a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  decided in Musk=E2=80=99s favor<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Friday, a federal jury in San Francisco too=
k just two hours to clear the Tesla Inc. chief executive officer of claims =
by investors that he defrauded them when he tweeted 4 1/2 years ago that he=
 was considering taking the company private and had =E2=80=9Cfunding secure=
d=E2=80=9D to make the deal happen. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk=E2=80=99s defense asked jurors to imagine=
 a world through the entrepreneur=E2=80=99s eyes, in which a $60 billion de=
al to take Tesla private could be done on a handshake. The jury learned of =
his relationship with Yasir Al-Rumayyan, the governor of Saudi Arabia=E2=80=
=99s Public Investment Fund, and a 2017 dinner with him joined by Softbank =
CEO Masayoshi Son, where taking Tesla private was discussed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk testified that the =E2=80=9Cfunding secur=
ed=E2=80=9D tweet was =E2=80=9Cabsolutely truthful,=E2=80=9D touting what h=
e described as an =E2=80=9Cunequivocal=E2=80=9D commitment by Saudi Arabia =
even though he had nothing in writing. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Witnesses, including senior Goldman Sachs exec=
utive Dan Dees and Silver Lake Management=E2=80=99s co-CEO, Egon Durban, to=
ld jurors that even a week after the tweet, they were still working to figu=
re out how the deal would be structured, including who would pay for it.=C2=
=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The trial was a bit odd because the judge had =
already decided that Musk=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cfunding secured=E2=80=9D tweet=
 was=C2=A0<em>false</em>, so the trial was technically about whether it was=
=C2=A0<em>material=C2=A0</em>to investors, whether they were deceived by th=
e tweet. But Musk did not quite say that he=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</em>going to=
 take Tesla private, only that he was considering it, which seems to have b=
een uncontroversially true. (He considers lots of things.) The falsehood wa=
s =E2=80=9Cfunding secured.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#fo=
otnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none=
 !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bloc=
k;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If you are an investor who bought the stock, you might say =E2=80=
=9CI bought the stock because Musk was considering taking it private, and I=
 was deceived,=E2=80=9D but that would be wrong: You were=C2=A0<em>not=C2=
=A0</em>deceived about that; he really was considering it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead you have to argue that you were deceiv=
ed by the funding bit. There are a couple of ways you could argue that, a c=
ouple of ways the =E2=80=9Cfunding secured=E2=80=9D could have tricked you:=
</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CI thought his funding was se=
cured, so the deal would happen if he wanted it to, but in fact he didn=E2=
=80=99t have funding and could never have done the deal.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</li=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CI thought =E2=80=98funding s=
ecured=E2=80=99 meant that he had already done a lot of work in structuring=
 the deal and was=C2=A0<em>serious=C2=A0</em>about doing the deal. I unders=
tood that nothing was=C2=A0<em>certain=C2=A0</em>and he could still change =
his mind, but I took the funding thing to indicate a certain seriousness, a=
nd I was deceived because he was just messing around.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Argument 1 was, I suppose, refuted by Musk=E2=
=80=99s testimony that he is very good at raising money and, if he=C2=A0<em=
>had=C2=A0</em>decided to move forward, it would have been no problem for h=
im to get funding, even though he did not in fact at that point have the mo=
ney. After Musk=E2=80=99s experience buying Twitter Inc. last year =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0when he really did snap his fingers and get together the $44 billi=
on needed to do the deal =E2=80=94=C2=A0I can=E2=80=99t object too strongly=
 to that.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Argument 2 was, I suppose, refuted by <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449/aHR0cHM6L=
y9naXptb2RvLmNvbS90ZXNsYS1lbG9uLW11c2stdHdpdHRlci10cmlhbC1raWQtZnVuZGluZy1z=
ZWN1cmVkLTE4NTAwNzIyMjU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdaae192e" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Musk=E2=
=80=99s lawyers=E2=80=99 arguments</a> to the effect of ahhhhh, come on, it=
 is Elon Musk, nothing is all that serious, he is winging it all the time, =
