<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what this means for the US Securities and =
Exchange Commission is a bit different. For the SEC, the way to turn everyt=
hing into securities fraud is to=C2=A0<em>require more disclosure</em>:=C2=
=A0If you require companies to make extensive disclosures about their carbo=
n emissions and environmental policies, then you have sort of de facto turn=
ed pollution into securities fraud, since a company that does a lot of terr=
ible pollution probably won=E2=80=99t have great disclosure about=C2=A0it.<=
a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
