arent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly, if the SEC had a rule that was like=
 =E2=80=9Ceach company must disclose, each quarter, the number of sexual ha=
rassment incidents that happened that quarter,=E2=80=9D then some companies=
 would say zero when the answer was not zero, and they=E2=80=99d get sued. =
The SEC=E2=80=99s rule would more or less automatically turn sexual harassm=
ent into securities fraud.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC does not have a rule like that, but it=
 can =E2=80=A6=C2=A0sort of =E2=80=A6=C2=A0make one up? Here is a fascinati=
ng <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30470906.258449=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0yMg/607f07ceef4=
