hing is securities fraud=E2=80=9D=C2=A0project is about limiting those cate=
gories, about expanding what is relevant to shareholders:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One rough way to think about the =
=E2=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud=E2=80=9D theory is that, once upon =
a time,=C2=A0<em>most=C2=A0</em>sorts of corporate behavior fell into these=
 categories =E2=80=94=C2=A0investors were presumed not to care about them, =
they weren=E2=80=99t discussed in filings, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0and the=C2=
=A0<em>only=C2=A0</em>area that mattered was, like, financial results. =E2=
=80=9CSecurities fraud=E2=80=9D meant lying about earnings. And then over t=
ime various areas of corporate behavior =E2=80=94=C2=A0executive ethics, cy=
bersecurity, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>became=C2=A0</em>things that companies=
 disclosed and investors were presumed to care about, and so now shareholde=
rs can sue companies if bad things happen in those areas.</p></blockquote>
